onal fossils while only $\\sim$3% of non-lensing control groups are. We\nalso find that $\\sim$23% of lensing systems are traditional fossil progenitors\ncompared to $\\sim$17% for the control sample. Our findings show that strong\nlensing systems are more likely to be fossil/pre-fossil systems than comparable\nnon-lensing systems. Cumulative galaxy luminosity functions of the lensing and\nnon-lensing groups also indicate a possible, fundamental difference between\nstrong lensing and non-lensing systems' galaxy populations with lensing systems\nhousing a greater number of bright galaxies even in the outskirts of groups.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Nov 2017 17:22:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-18"}
